welcome to nishamadhulika.com

00:00:06.580 --> 00:00:15.677
chole are prepared with kabuli chanas,desi chana and dried peas (matar).

00:00:16.013 --> 00:00:18.410
today we will make matar chole.

00:00:18.665 --> 00:00:24.229
let's see what all ingerdients are required for making matar chole.

00:00:24.419 --> 00:00:29.779
matar - 1.5 cup (250 grams) (soaked for 8-10 hours)

00:00:30.012 --> 00:00:33.004
after soaking in water matar get double in size.

00:00:34.333 --> 00:00:41.387
paste - 3 tomato,1-2 green chilly and 1 inch piece ginger

00:00:41.609 --> 00:00:43.593
turmeric powder - 1/2 tsp

00:00:44.112 --> 00:00:46.104
cumin seeds - 1/2 tsp

00:00:46.504 --> 00:00:47.861
asafoetida - 1-2 pinch

00:00:48.339 --> 00:00:51.458
salt - as per taste (1 tsp)

00:00:51.763 --> 00:00:53.985
coriander powder - 1 tsp

00:00:54.322 --> 00:00:57.377
red chilly powder - less then 1/4 tsp

00:00:57.800 --> 00:01:00.792
garam masala - less then 1/4 tsp

00:01:01.337 --> 00:01:04.265
green coriander - 1-2 tbsp (finely chopped)

00:01:04.745 --> 00:01:06.641
oil - 1-2 tbsp

00:01:07.749 --> 00:01:10.241
boil the peas first.

00:01:10.550 --> 00:01:19.811
for this place peas in cooker and add 1-1.5 cup water.

00:01:25.042 --> 00:01:28.026
add more water if needed.

00:01:31.341 --> 00:01:41.841
add baking soda and half the amount of water.

00:01:49.106 --> 00:01:55.448
close the cooker and turn off the gas.

00:01:56.650 --> 00:01:59.777
cook matar chole until it whistles for once.

00:02:02.092 --> 00:02:04.005
turn off the gas now.

00:02:14.230 --> 00:02:17.261
meanwhile prepare masala for chole.

00:02:18.244 --> 00:02:21.990
add oil in preheated pan.

00:02:25.824 --> 00:02:27.958
when oil gets hot add cumin seeds

00:02:33.729 --> 00:02:50.950
after sauteing cumin seeds add turmeric powder,coriander powder and tomto-ginger-chilly paste.

00:03:02.831 --> 00:03:08.450
saute the masala until oil starts floating on the surface.

00:03:09.148 --> 00:03:10.870
stir after regular intervals.

00:03:10.949 --> 00:03:13.569
it will take 4-5 minutes in sauteing masala.

00:03:24.519 --> 00:03:38.156
if you wish to use onion,then finely chop them and after sauting cumin seeds add onion and roast until they turn pinkish in color.

00:03:38.747 --> 00:03:43.993
similarly prepare masala.

00:03:49.888 --> 00:03:54.626
masala is ready,add salt as well.

00:04:19.728 --> 00:04:22.490
add boiled matar in the masala.

00:04:29.718 --> 00:04:37.230
add water as per your preference for making gravy.

00:04:43.009 --> 00:04:44.985
add garam masala.

00:04:54.221 --> 00:05:01.718
cover and cook for 2 minutes on low flame so that all spices get absorbed in the matar.

00:05:10.929 --> 00:05:18.615
chole are ready;add green coriander into them.

00:05:19.103 --> 00:05:24.453
add coriander in the end so that its fragrance stays for long in the sabzi.

00:05:25.106 --> 00:05:27.042
matar chole are ready.

00:05:29.674 --> 00:05:32.889
we used 200 grams matar chole for making this sabzi.

00:05:33.154 --> 00:05:38.725
this mauch quantity of chole can be served to 4-5 famliy members.

00:05:39.119 --> 00:05:43.961
serve matar chole with chapatti,parantha,naan or rice.

00:05:44.237 --> 00:05:50.443
